SIMPLE: second-sight
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Second-sight
<hw>Sec"ond-sight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The power of
discerning what is not visible to the physical eye, or of foreseeing
future events, esp. such as are of a disastrous kind; the capacity of a
seer; prophetic vision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was seized with a fit of <qex>second-sight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor less availed his optic sleight,⟦br⟧
And Scottish gift of <qex>second-sight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Second-sighted</ent>⟦br⟧
